# `nypr-ui/hero`

A hero image layout with optional gradients and sticky headers. Exposes multiple contextual components that can be used to layout content.
"}}

{{code-snippet name="hero.hbs"}}

{{md-text text="
## `nypr-ui/hero` params
The top level `nypr-ui/hero` component accepts two params. 

key | default | description
--- | --- | ---
sticky | false | Stick the hero top to the top of screen when it scrolls past.

## `nypr-ui/hero` yields

key name | yields | description
--- | --- | ---
`.top` | `.left`, `.right` | header area. this will stick to the top of the page if `sticky=true`.
`.top.left` | N/A | left area. sticks to the upper left in stuck state.
`.top.right` | N/A | right side of header. disappears in stuck state.
`.image` | N/A | Hero image. If the breakpoint matches, the image will be a background image on the top-level component element, otherwise it will render as an image element.
`.headline` | N/A | Intended for headline use. Renders font very large.
`.blurb` | N/A | Renders with a small font size.
`.footer` | `.lockup` | Renders elements spaced apart.
`.footer.lockup` | N/A | Aligned to far right of the footer area and \"locked up\" to the upper right in the stuck state.

## `nypr-ui/hero/image`
The hero image is rendered as a background element on `.nypr-ui__hero` (the top level component) or as an `<img />` element, depending on whether the value of the `breakpoint` attribute is set. The default for `breakpoint` is `(min-width: 801px)`, but can be overridden at run time.

"}}

